                                    <strong>Over&ndash;the&ndash;counter options</strong>
                                    are the least expensive; expect to pay anywhere from $20 to $150.
                                </li>

                                <li>
                                    <strong>Dentist&ndash;Supervised At&ndash;Home Treatments</strong>
                                    can vary depending on your location and how much work you need to be done but expect to pay 
                                    roughly $150&ndash;$300 per set of teeth (upper and lower) or $350&ndash;$600 for the entire mouth.                                    
                                </li>

                                <li>
                                    <strong>In&ndash;Office Treatments</strong>
                                    range from $200&ndash;$500 for one arch or $500&ndash;$1,000 for the entire mouth.
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </p>

